- Only `<` before the bracket is optional 
- Doesn't handle all variants of IE conditional comments
- The regex can be bypassed with variations like `[ if IE]` (space before `if` not matched since `\s*` is AFTER `[`)
- Missing `\s*` before `if` — wait, actually looking again: `\[\s*(?:end)?if` - the `\s*` IS before `(?:end)?if`, so `[ if IE]` WOULD be matched

